This module adopts the same governance shape as terraform-aws-vpc,
terraform-aws-iam, terraform-aws-s3, terraform-aws-kms, and
terraform-aws-rds: unified Foundation Plan §15.2 tagging, the central
reusable CI workflow in devotica-labs/terraform-shared-config, and
conftest policies from devotica-labs/terraform-policies.

Defaults are aligned with fintech compliance requirements:

- enable_deletion_protection on by default (the cost of accidental
  deletion >>> the friction of toggling this off).
- drop_invalid_header_fields on by default (HTTP-smuggling mitigation,
  CIS AWS Foundations 5.1.x).
- desync_mitigation_mode = defensive (AWS-recommended balance for the
  HTTP-desync class of attacks).
- HTTP/2 on by default.
- preserve_host_header on by default (apps that depend on the original
  Host header — multi-tenant routing, signed URLs — need it).
- Default SSL policy ELBSecurityPolicy-TLS13-1-2-2021-06 (TLS 1.2/1.3
  modern policy that drops every cipher with known weakness).
- HTTPS listeners are required to supply certificate_arn (validation
  refuses HTTPS without a cert).

Listener rules (path-based and host-based routing) and authentication
(Cognito / OIDC) are deferred to v0.2 — see the README scope table.
Network Load Balancers live in a sister module (terraform-aws-nlb) —
ALB and NLB share enough surface to be confusing if combined.

